# <type>[optional scope]: <description>
#
# [optional body]
#
# [optional footer(s)]
#
# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be:
#   feat     (new feature)
#   fix      (bug fix)
#   docs     (documentation)
#   style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc)
#   refactor (refactoring production code)
#   test     (adding tests, refactoring test)
#   chore    (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc)
#   perf     (performance improvements)
#   ci       (CI/CD pipeline changes)
#   build    (build system changes)
#   revert   (reverting previous commit)
#
# Scope examples:
#   feat(ledger): add new transaction validation
#   fix(payments): resolve connector timeout issue
#   docs(api): update endpoint documentation
#   refactor(auth): simplify authentication logic
#
# Breaking changes should include BREAKING CHANGE: in the footer
# Issues should be referenced in the footer: Closes #123
#
# Examples:
#   feat: add user registration endpoint
#   fix(payments): resolve stripe webhook validation
#   docs: update installation instructions
#   BREAKING CHANGE: remove deprecated v1 API endpoints